
Jazz Semiconductor userware  - Information on importing spice netlist as "black-box"
______________________________________________________________________

In order to allow reuse of previous designs from other (including Cadence)
design systems, where only the subcircuit view (in spice subckt netlist 
format) is available, you must create stopping views and the associated
CDF SimInfo for each view. For example, to use Spectre, you'll need
a "spectre" view and simInfo section in addition to the symbol view.
For LVS using the Jazz Calibre CBR netlister, you need a spectreS view and simInfo.
For LVS using Assura, you need an auLvs view and simInfo.
For LVS using Calibre Interactive, you need an auCdl view and simInfo.

To run simulation in "spectre" view:
Please see Cadence Virtuoso Analog Design Environment
User's Guide for more information.
1. create symbol view of the imported subckt block with pins 
   (number of pins must equal that of the subckt)
2. create "spectre" view (use "library manager" to copy "symbol" 
   view to "spectre" view)
3. Add the following CDF parameters, using TOOLS->CDF->EDIT:
   CDF Type -> Base
   Library Name -> Library_Name
   Cell Name -> Cell_Name
   Simulation Information -> Edit 
     Choose Simulator -> spectre
     componentName       subckt_name
     termOrder           block_pin_order (must match pin order of the subckt)
   OK
4. Define model path in Analog Artist as follows: 
     Setup -> Model Libraries -> Model Library File-> model_file_path
     -> Add -> OK
5. Netlist format:
   A. spectre format is recommended.
   B. spice/hspice format file may be acceptable, but it will be read
      and parsed by Spectre.

To run simulation in "hspiceS" view or other Socketed simulator.
Please see Cadence Sourcelink Solution 1835032 and the Virtuoso
Analog Design Environment User's Guide for more information.
1. create symbol view of the imported subckt block with pins 
   (number of pins must equal that of the subckt)
2. create "hspiceS" view (use "library manager" to copy "symbol" 
   view to "hspiceS" view)
3. Add the following CDF parameters, using TOOLS->CDF->EDIT:
   CDF Type -> Base
   Library Name -> Library_Name
   Cell Name -> Cell_Name
   Component Parameters ->
     _____________________________________________________
     Name                Prompt_Name         Default_Value
     _____________________________________________________
     macro               macro               subckt_name
     macroArgumentStyle  macroArgumentStyle  includeFile
     _____________________________________________________

   Simulation Information -> Edit 
     Choose Simulator -> hspiceS
     netlistProcedure    ansSpiceSubcktCall
     termOrder           block_pin_order (must match pin order of the subckt)
     namePrefix          X
   OK
4. Define model path in Analog Artist as follows: 
     Setup -> Model Path
5. Netlist format in hspice/spice format is recommended.
